WEBVTT

00:01.601 --> 00:03.335
Hey. Hey, guys, listen.

00:03.370 --> 00:04.837
Leslie's gonna
walk in and say something

00:04.871 --> 00:07.152
that sounds very boring but
is actually a really big deal.

00:07.222 --> 00:09.390
So when I give the signal,
just everybody cheer like crazy.

00:09.424 --> 00:10.558
Here we go.

00:10.592 --> 00:12.893
Well, someone just
officially enrolled

00:12.928 --> 00:15.496
in the Senior Executive Service
Development Candidate Program

00:15.530 --> 00:17.331
at the Department
of the Interior.

00:17.365 --> 00:18.732
[all cheering]

00:18.767 --> 00:20.034
Surprise!

00:20.068 --> 00:21.335
Thanks.
It's a big deal.

00:21.369 --> 00:23.471
So my promotion is official.

00:23.505 --> 00:24.905
We need to find
a place in D.C.

00:24.940 --> 00:26.307
because we're gonna be
splitting our time.

00:26.341 --> 00:27.975
I guess now is
as good a time as any

00:28.009 --> 00:29.510
make my announcement.

00:29.544 --> 00:31.846
Joe and I just closed
on a house in Seattle.

00:31.880 --> 00:33.180
- Whoa!
- Oh, my God!

00:33.215 --> 00:34.515
Cheers.

00:34.549 --> 00:36.851
Well, actually
I have an announcement too.

00:36.885 --> 00:38.786
After all these years
in government,

00:38.820 --> 00:41.255
I've decided to finally retire.

00:41.289 --> 00:42.890
This is about people
who are moving, Garry.

00:42.924 --> 00:44.558
- Not everything is about you.
- Good point.

00:44.593 --> 00:45.793
Everyone's scattering.

00:45.827 --> 00:47.428
Well, look at it this way,

00:47.462 --> 00:49.263
bad news comes in threes, right?

00:49.297 --> 00:50.898
We're leaving,
April and Andy are leaving,

00:50.932 --> 00:52.533
Donna's leaving, that's three.

00:52.567 --> 00:53.834
Also I'm retiring.

00:53.869 --> 00:55.469
That's three, Garry.

00:55.504 --> 00:57.571
But we're probably due
for some good news.

00:57.606 --> 00:58.773
Good evening.

00:58.807 --> 01:00.341
I come to you tonight
with some good news...

01:00.375 --> 01:01.709
Hey.

01:01.743 --> 01:04.044
Is not a sentence I will be
saying to you right now,

01:04.078 --> 01:07.982
because beloved Pawnee Mayor
Walter Gunderson has died.

01:08.016 --> 01:10.951
[all gasp]
[sighs]

01:10.986 --> 01:13.788
Well, you jinxed us, Garry.
Thanks a lot.

01:13.822 --> 01:16.724
[triumphant music]

01:16.758 --> 01:24.632
